HEADWORD: Bondholder
<hw>Bond"hold`er</hw> <pr>(-h⟦omac⟧ld`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A person who holds the bonds of a public or private corporation for
the payment of money at a certain time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

